#: includes/settings-page.php:340
msgid "Cloudflare Cache Sync"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:349
msgid "Synchronize the Cloudflare cache purges to keep both caches aligned."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:352
msgid "Independent of \"Auto Purge\". When ON, the Cloudflare cache is purged whenever the Nginx cache is purged (whether for single URLs or the entire cache)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:355
msgid "Requires the official Cloudflare WordPress plugin with APO or PSC enabled and proper authentication."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:363
msgid "Redis Object Cache Sync"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:372
msgid "Synchronize the Redis Object Cache with the Nginx cache to keep both layers aligned."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:375
msgid "Independent of \"Auto Purge\". When ON: \"Purge All\" (Admin, REST) also flushes the Redis object cache, but only if \"Auto Preload\" is ON."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:378
msgid "When ON: \"Preload All\" (Admin, REST, Cron) always flushes the Redis object cache."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:381
msgid "Flushing Redis cache only makes sense as part of the Nginx Purge+Preload chain or direct Cache Preload actions."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:384
msgid "A purge-only operation (without Preload) should leave the Redis cache warm."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:387
msgid "Requires the Redis Object Cache plugin to be installed, configured, and connected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:395
msgid "Purge Scope"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:399
msgid "Extends single-URL purges only — has no effect on full cache purge (Purge All, REST API, or Scheduled Purge). Fires on every single-URL purge: automatically via Auto Purge events and manually via the Admin Bar on-page button, the Advanced Tab, or the front-end purge button."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:417
msgid "Vary: Accept-Encoding"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:421
msgid "Double Cache Issue"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:423
msgid "If you encounter this issue "
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:425
msgid "→ See Help tab for fix and full explanation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:442
msgid "Enable this feature to automatically preload the cache after a purge. This ensures fast load times by proactively caching content before the first visitor arrives."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:443
msgid "When enabled, your website will automatically rebuild the cache with the latest content, ensuring a high cache hit rate even for frequently changing pages."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:444
msgid "This process is triggered after any purge: automatically via the Auto Purge feature, manually via \"Purge All\", or via a single-URL purge from the Admin Bar or Advanced Tab."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:445
msgid "To trigger Preload Related Pages (Purge Scope) when Auto Purge is ON, this setting must be turned ON."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:460
msgid "Preload also Nginx cache for Mobile devices separately. This feature supports for both entire and single POST/PAGE cache events."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:461
msgid "Only enable if you have different content, themes or configurations for Mobile and Desktop devices and need to warm the cache for both."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:462
msgid "If enabled, this feature always triggers automatically when Preload actions are called via Rest, Cron or Admin, regardless of whether Auto Preload or Auto Purge are enabled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:463
msgid "If only Auto Preload is enabled, it also triggers automatically after any Purge action: REST API, Admin Bar, Advanced Tab, or Auto Purge events."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:464
msgid "When both Auto Purge and Auto Preload are enabled, it triggers automatically whenever cache is purged — whether by Auto Purge events, Purge All, single-URL purges from the Admin Bar or Advanced Tab, or via REST."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:467
msgid "Note:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:468
msgid "The Mobile Preload action will begin after the main Preload process completes via the WordPress Cron job. As a result, the Mobile Preload action may start with a delay. To track the status of this process, please refer to the log section of the plugin."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:475
msgid "Mobile User Agent"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:480
msgid "Define the User-Agent sent during the mobile preload pass. Must match the User-Agent your Nginx cache key uses to distinguish mobile from desktop variants."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:481
msgid "Only relevant when Preload Mobile is enabled. If your cache key does not vary on User-Agent, leave this at the default value."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:484
#: includes/settings-page.php:574
#: includes/settings-page.php:593
#: includes/settings-page.php:796
msgid "Reset Default"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:487
msgid "Click the button to restore the built-in mobile User-Agent string. After plugin updates, reset first to pick up any changes, then reapply your custom value."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:502
msgid "Enable the preload watchdog. When active, watchdog monitors the preload and fires post-preload tasks immediately when preload finishes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:503
msgid "Especially useful on zero-traffic or fully-cached sites where WP-Cron may be delayed. If disabled, post-preload tasks are handled entirely by WP-Cron."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:504
msgid "Recommended for users have cron delay issues. The watchdog is lightweight and exits automatically once preload completes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:510
msgid "Use Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:516
msgid "Routes preload requests through your HTTP proxy (e.g. mitmproxy) so the cache is warmed via the proxy."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:517
msgid "Enable if you need proxy features (debugging/inspection, custom headers, mTLS, fixed egress IP, corporate proxy, DNS overrides)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:518
msgid "If enabling, follow the Help tab for example use cases, keep in mind to set the proxy URL/PORT below."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:519
msgid "Note: A proxy adds latency to cache preload."
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:525
msgid "Proxy Host"
msgstr ""

#: includes/settings-page.php:529
